## ğŸ› ï¸ My Hands-On Example for OpenMRS

If I were leading an OpenMRS deployment in a HIPAA-covered environment, here are two controls I would mandate:

 **Administrative safeguard:**  
â€œEstablish weekly reviews of OpenMRS audit logs for unauthorized or anomalous access.â€

 **Technical safeguard:**  
â€œEnable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for all OpenMRS administrative accounts and remote users.â€

Why? Because **audit log reviews detect misuse** and **MFA blocks stolen credentials** â€” both are critical for reducing risk of ePHI breaches.

